HEADWORD: Sankhya
<hw>Sankh"ya</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A Hindu system of
philosophy which refers all things to soul and a rootless germ called
<xex>prakriti</xex>, consisting of three elements, goodness, passion,
and darkness.</def> <rj><au>Whitworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

